    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the bacon is cooking, add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the squash is fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon is crispy, add the <strong>chopped leeks</strong> with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>grated cheese </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, until the cheese is melted, and set aside off the heat \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong>, unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rolled pastry</strong> to the tray[s] and prick it all over with a fork (this will stop it getting a soggy bottom!)</p><p>Top the <strong>pastry</strong> with the <strong>cheesy filling</strong>, leaving a 2cm border</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fold the <strong>pastry border</strong> over the edge of the filling</p><p>Tip: Start from one corner and work around in one direction, overlapping the pastry each time</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You will need to make multiple galettes!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-22 min or until the pastry is golden, cooked through and the edges have puffed up \u2013 this is your<strong> cheesy bacon & butternut squash galette</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-and-butternut-squash-galette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Set aside the <strong>cheesy bacon & butternut squash galette</strong> for 2-3 min for the flavours to develop</p><p>Serve the <strong>cheesy bacon & butternut squash galette</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad </strong>to the side and drizzle over your<strong> balsamic vinegar </strong>and a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
